All things are possible, but not all things are advisable. While I think th=
at there is fairly wide agreement that JavaDoc in the source file is good, =
I would suggest that tests inside the source file are not.

To my mind, the=
re is a valuable separation when you have the tests in a separate file. Eac=
h file is able to be specific and short. The actual object being tested can=
 just get on with doing it&#39;s purpose in life and the test can concentrate o=
n driving it hard. Also, remember that a test is against a behaviour rather=
 than a method, so some tests may have legitimate reasons to test methods f=
rom several objects as part of testing a behaviour.

